The paper proposes a graph neural network (GNN) based model for overlapping community detection, which is a fundamental problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the main focus of the paper. The paper also deals with graph-related tasks, which makes cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a model that is effective, scalable, and robust to hyperparameter settings, which suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well.
